The paper deals with developing an audiovisual deep residual network for personality trait recognition from videos, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with multimodal learning, which involves multiple modalities such as audio and video, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions that the network is trained end-to-end, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with predicting personality traits, which involves social and behavioral sciences, making cs.SD (Social and Information Networks) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with recognizing personality traits from videos, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI), making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another likely sub-category.
